## Parallel Sessions

You can run multiple Claude Code sessions on this repository simultaneously, **as long as each session is on a different git branch**. Each branch has its own isolated checkpoint file (`.claude/memory/context-{branch}.md`), so sessions never overwrite each other's state.

**Safe — recommended parallel workflow:**

| Session | Branch | Doing |
|---------|--------|-------|
| A | `feature/feat-001-login` | `/implement FEAT-001` |
| B | `develop` (or `feature/feat-002-signup`) | `/refine FEAT-002` |

Session A implements on its feature branch. Session B refines a different spec from develop or its own branch. No conflict.

**Not safe — same branch, two sessions:**

Two sessions both on `feature/feat-001-login` will race to write the same checkpoint file and may conflict on source files. Don't do it.

**Rule of thumb:** one session per branch. Keep implementation sessions on their feature branches. Use a separate session on `develop` for refinement, drafting, and brainstorming of other specs.

