## Context Management

Long sessions (especially `/implement` on a non-trivial feature) can approach the context limit. Claude cannot trigger `/compact` itself — the working rules are:

**Keep compaction safe at every natural boundary** (after each subtask commit, after a review cycle, after a refine completes): commit and push all changes, keep the branch context file (`.claude/memory/context-{branch}.md`) current, and make spec checkboxes reflect actual progress. Then automatic compaction — or a user-run `/compact` at a phase boundary — never loses state.

**Avoid bloat**: bulky reading and full test runs go to subagents; raw logs and large files stay out of the main context.

After any compaction, Claude reads the branch context file to re-orient before continuing.

