## Branching

This project uses: **{{BRANCHING_MODEL}}**

### Common rules (both models)
| Branch | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `feature/feat-001-title` | Feature branches — one per spec |
| `fix/bug-042-title` | Bug fix branches |
| `chore/description` | Maintenance work |

- **Pushing to feature branches is always allowed** — push after every commit (backup, visibility).
- **The quality gate sits at the merge, not the push**: merging into the integration branch happens only via `/pr` (CI green + AI reviews passed).
- Branches are created by `/implement` and deleted by `/pr` after merge.

### main-only
- Feature branches merge into `main` via `/pr`.
- `/release` tags directly on `main`.

### git flow
- `develop` is the integration branch — all feature/fix branches merge into `develop` via `/pr`.
- `master` contains **only released states**: `/release` tests `develop`, fixes remaining bugs, then merges `develop` → `master` and tags the merge commit. The tip of `master` always equals the latest release.
- Nobody pushes directly to `develop` or `master` (exception: the release merge performed by `/release`).
